    <h1>A Synthetic Approach to Markov Kernels</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Tobias Fritz · 2020 · <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1908.07021"><img src="/reading/arxiv.webp" alt="arxiv" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/> arXiv:1908.07021</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Stochastic functions form a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category_(mathematics)"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>category</a> with copy and discard. Copying detects whether a function is deterministic or stochastic.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- What's a Markov category -->
    <h3>What's a Markov category</h3>

    <!-- SVG: Copy and discard structural morphisms -->
